quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  7,171,"And [remember] when We raised the mountain over them as if it were a dark cloud, and they thought that it would fall upon them, “Hold fast to what We have given you and observe its teachings, so that you may fear Allah.”"
  7,172,"And [remember] when your Lord brought forth from the loins of the children of Adam their offspring and made them testify about themselves [asking], “Am I not your Lord?” They said, “Yes indeed; We testify.” [We did so] lest you should say on the Day of Resurrection, “We were unaware of this,”"
  7,173,"Or that you say, “It was our forefathers before us who associated partners with Allah, and we are their offspring who came after them. Will you then destroy us for the falsehood that they invented?”"
  7,174,"This is how We make the verses clear, so that they may return"
  7,175,"And relate to them [O Prophet] the story of the one whom We gave knowledge of Our revelations, but he abandoned it, so Satan took hold of him and he became one of the deviants"
  7,176,"If We had willed, We could have elevated him thereby, but he clung to the [life of the] earth and followed his desires. His likeness is that of a dog: if you attack it, it pants with its tongue lolling, and if you leave it, it still pants. Such is the example of the people who reject Our revelations. Therefore relate the stories, so that they may reflect"
  7,177,"How evil is the likeness of people who rejected Our verses, and it is themselves that they have wronged"
  7,178,"Whoever Allah guides is rightly guided; and whoever He causes to stray, it is they who are the losers"
  7,179,"We have surely created for Hell many jinn and humans. They have hearts with which they do not understand, eyes with which they do not see, and ears with which they do not hear. They are like cattle, rather, they are more astray. It is they who are the heedless"
  7,180,"Allah has the Most Beautiful Names, so call upon Him by them, and leave those who profane His Names. They will be recompensed for what they used to do"
  7,181,And among those whom We created is a group that guides others with the truth and establishes justice therewith
  7,182,"As for those who reject Our signs, We will gradually lead them to destruction without them realizing it"
  7,183,"I will give them respite, but My plan is firm"
  7,184,"Have they not reflected that their fellow [Prophet] is not insane? He is none but a clear warner"
  7,185,"Have they not observed the dominions of the heavens and earth and all that Allah has created, and that the end of their term might be near? In what message after this [Qur’an] will they then believe"
  7,186,"Whoever Allah causes to stray, there is none to guide him; He will leave them to wander blindly in their transgression"
  7,187,"They ask you [O Prophet] about the Hour, “When will it come to pass?” Say, “Its knowledge is only with my Lord. None can reveal its due time except Him. It will be heavy on the heavens and earth; it will only come to you by surprise.” They ask you as if you are well-aware of it. Say, “Its knowledge is only with Allah, but most people do not know.”"
  7,188,"Say, “I have no power to benefit or harm myself, except what Allah wills. If I had knowledge of the unseen, I would have acquired much good, and no evil would have touched me. I am only a warner and bearer of glad tidings for people who believe.”"